  "response": "Yes, money laundering is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It is considered a serious financial crime and is punishable by law. Money laundering involves the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, or other criminal acts) appear legitimate by funneling it through a series of transactions or businesses.\n\nGovernments and international organizations have established strict regulations and anti-money laundering (AML) laws to detect, prevent, and prosecute such activities. Penalties for money laundering can include hefty fines, seizure of assets, and imprisonment.\n\nIf you have any concerns or questions about financial regulations, it\u2019s always a good idea to consult a legal or financial professional.",
